assistant_prompt:
 ve
menuswitch between css selectors or even with a select list

A:

All CSS properties and selectors are case-sensitive. So, you want a { property: value; } instead of a property: value;.

A:

Try:
#content .side-bar-menu-link-submenu-inner li a {
    color: #fff;
}

or
#content .side-bar-menu-link-submenu-inner li a.active {
    color: #fff;
}

or
#content .side-bar-menu-link-submenu-inner li a:hover {
    color: #fff;
}

or
#content .side-bar-menu-link-submenu-inner li a:active {
    color: #fff;
}

A:

I had this problem, and it was due to the fact that some of the CSS was being included from the theme files as well as the theme customizer.  I fixed it with this in functions.php...
function fix_custom_css_selectors( $classes ) {
    $new_classes = array();
    foreach( $classes as $class_name => $class_value ) {
        if ( is_array( $class_value ) ) {
            $new_classes[ $class_name ] = $class_value;
        } else {
            $new_classes[ $class_name ] = $class_value;
        }
    }
    return $new_classes;
}
add_filter( 'style_loader_src', 'fix_custom_css_selectors', 10, 1 );

The array is not quite what I want, but it definitely fixes it.

