I feel like this shouldn't be necessary, but I'll give it a shot.
You can use the following rule for OpenSearch:
<opensearch:Query type="application/opensearchdescription+xml"
        xmlns:opensearch="http://a9.com/-/spec/opensearch/1.1/">
    <opensearch:QueryDescription
        applyingAuthority="example.com"
        responseEncoding="UTF-8"
        >
        <opensearch:TotalResults>20</opensearch:TotalResults>
    </opensearch:QueryDescription>
</opensearch:Query>

Then, you can use the following XSLT to get the description element:
<xsl:template match="opensearch:QueryDescription">
    <description>
        <xsl:value-of select="." />
    </description>
</xsl:template>

See it working here: http://xsltransform.net/pNZ7N6N

