How to get a substring from a string in PHP

I have a string:
$string = 'The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog';

I want to get the substring from $string which is:
The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog

I used the following code:
$string = 'The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog';
$index = strpos($string, 'jumps over');
$start = $index;

But it returns:
$start = 0;

Because it counts the first letter of the word 'jumps' from the string. But it doesn't count the letters after 'jumps' from the string.

A:

$string = 'The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog';

$pos = strpos($string, 'jumps');
if (false !== $pos) {
    $word = substr($string, $pos);
    $pos = strpos($word, ' over');
    if (false !== $pos) {
        $new_word = substr($word, 0, $pos);
        $result = $new_word . ' jumps';
    } else {
        $result = $word;
    }
} else {
    $result = $string;
}

echo $result;

A:

You can use the function strpos to find the position where the word jumps is

