assistant_prompt:
(socketio)

I'm trying to push two diagrams into a running websocket server, but I don't really understand how I would do this.
I know how to get an image(file) and how to pass it to the server but I don't really know how to merge these diagrams into the running server.

A:

You can use the fs module.
It allows you to create a file with a stream on it.
You could create a small script that creates the file, for example.
You could then use the fs.createWriteStream function to create a stream on the file.
Here is a simple example that will create a file with an image in it.
var fs = require('fs');

fs.writeFile('myFile.jpg', 'Hello World!', function(err) {
  console.log('File created!');
});

fs.createWriteStream('myFile.jpg');

If you want to use the image as background, you could use a canvas.
You could use the canvas.toDataURL function to get the image as data.
You could then use that data, and the fs.createWriteStream function again to create the file.
Here is a simple example using the canvas.
var fs = require('fs');
var canvas = document.createElement('canvas');
canvas.width = 100;
canvas.height = 100;
canvas.getContext('2d').drawImage(document.body, 0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);
var dataURL = canvas.toDataURL();
fs.writeFile('myFile.png', dataURL, function(err) {
  console.log('File created!');
});

fs.createWriteStream('myFile.png');

